  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3506017105?book_show_action=true">Aug 20, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jen" href="/user/show/7467348-jen">Jen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781496725837" href="/book/show/42249041-the-pieces-we-keep">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3506017105&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3506017105" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9929828955708482458">This is my first Kristina McMorris novel and while I found it compelling enough to finish I’m not sure I would read more from her. I agree with other reviewers that Vivian’s love scenes were a bit overdone and cliché. I also found Audra hard to relate to because she seemed so clumsy and stupid with her words and actions. Lastly I found the whole ending to be trite and at the same time unresolved-even though the characters’ stories conveniently merge and the book had a nice happy ending, I don’t </span>
  <span id="freeText9929828955708482458" style="display:none">This is my first Kristina McMorris novel and while I found it compelling enough to finish I’m not sure I would read more from her. I agree with other reviewers that Vivian’s love scenes were a bit overdone and cliché. I also found Audra hard to relate to because she seemed so clumsy and stupid with her words and actions. Lastly I found the whole ending to be trite and at the same time unresolved-even though the characters’ stories conveniently merge and the book had a nice happy ending, I don’t understand how Jack’s problem just went away and so much was left open-ended regarding the reincarnation theme. It’s like the author didn’t know how to resolve that so she just kind of dismissed it after making such a big deal about it in the first half of the story. <br /><br />Maybe I am too pragmatic but after such an interesting war story (can’t say the same for present story) I was looking for a little more than an “everyone finds out the truth through some random third party and then everyone loves everyone and becomes BFFs and all of our problems magically go away” ending. I know it’s fiction but really???</span>
  <a data-text-id="9929828955708482458" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
